Comment: Project by ministry of agriculture. Technical issues. Water does not stay in dam. Big flood damaged the dam as not constructed very well.

Channel eroded through very friable orange rhyolite. Dyke running through the dam aligment, possibly the design assumed the dyke would prevent erosion around the sides of the structure. Project started in 2016 and finished in 2020.  The flows deposited the sediment behind the dam a few days before we came.  Also sediment deposited in 2020. When the dam failed in 2020 they sent letter to Ministry of Environment but nothing done to remediate the structure. No sediment behind the dam when it was first built.
Goat droppings in the wadi sediment.
Septic tank for the school teachers house.

Comment: Reservoir. Metal incoming pipe. They know it's full when it overflows.  Two of the reservoirs at the BH is enough to fill this reservoir.  They phone for the pump to be turned off. It takes 3 hours to fill in winter and 5 hours in summer.  When the reservoir is empty there is an agent who controls opening the water to the different neighborhoods. One of the neighborhoods is 250 households and the other is 350 households.  Filled every day.  Each day water supplied to a different neighborhood.  The pump has an automatic shut off. Built in 1995.  Two water supply parts of village alternate daily.  approx 70m3 tank.  paced 20m 22 degrees angle. Circumference 21m. 450 houses have pipes to their houses. 150 not connected.   Big pipes about 60cm under surface when installed.  every 20m small pipes come off big pipes. if someone wants their own connection they request from the prefecture and pay.  Built by Ministry of Agriculture Hydraulic Division.  Water is free.  Ministry of Agriculture responsible for maintainance.
